gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 132, Mavericks 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Mavericks, 132-109, as they won their seventh consecutive game and improved to 26-18. Devin Booker led the Suns with 46 points (17-23 FG, 6-10 3PT), seven rebounds, and three assists as Bradley Beal (20 points, seven rebounds, seven assists) and Kevin Durant (12 points, 10 rebounds, seven assists, two blocks) totaled 32 points. Luka Doncic led the Mavericks with 34 points, eight rebounds, and nine assists. The Mavericks move to 24-20 with the loss.
